# Arabic replies - LTR code first, RTL prose second

## When this applies

- User message is **primarily Arabic** -> layout below (RTL-only if no technical content).
- User message is **English only** (or user asks for English) -> normal LTR; no rtl wrapper.
- **Mixed** -> technical content in Zone LTR; Arabic in Zone RTL.

## Problem (Cursor chat)

`dir="rtl"` on a parent makes **later** fenced code and citations render RTL even after `</div>`. Backtick lines **inside** the rtl div are also corrupted. When the reply includes code, Zone LTR must be **first** and wrap all technical content.

## Zone LTR (first, when needed)

Use only if the reply includes **any** of: code citations, fenced code, backtick tokens, paths, env vars, step keys, shell commands, JSON, or a table whose cells are mostly Latin/code.

```html
<div dir="ltr" lang="en" style="direction: ltr; unicode-bidi: isolate;">
```

Close with `</div>`.

**Tables with paths, step keys, or code in cells** -> markdown table in Zone LTR, not Zone RTL.

## Zone RTL (second, or only zone)

When the user message is primarily Arabic:

```html
<div dir="rtl" lang="ar">
```

**Allowed:** Arabic prose, Arabic **markdown pipe tables**, Arabic lists.

**Not allowed:** backticks, fenced code, code citations, file paths, env lines.

Close with `</div>`.

If the reply has **no** technical content, use **only** Zone RTL (do not open an empty Zone LTR).

## Referring to code

In Zone RTL, point to the block **above** (e.g. see code block above). Paths and citations live only in Zone LTR.

## Arabic tables

- Use **markdown pipe tables** in Zone RTL for Arabic data.
- **Accepted:** cell text may still read LTR in Cursor chat — **ignore**; keep the markdown table unless the user asks for another format.
- No backticks in Arabic cells; code-heavy tables belong in Zone LTR.

## Quick reference

| Content | Zone |
|---------|------|
| Code citations, fences, backticks, paths | LTR first |
| Arabic prose, Arabic markdown tables | RTL |
| Latin/code table | LTR |
| Arabic only, no code | RTL only |

## Prohibited

- Code or backticks inside `dir="rtl"`.
- Technical lines after rtl `</div>` without a preceding ltr wrapper.
- Arabic-primary replies without `<div dir="rtl" lang="ar">`.
- Forcing Arabic on English-only messages.
- List/card/HTML table workarounds instead of markdown tables unless the user requests them.
